The paper discusses the linguistic operations of synecdoche and metonymy in naming strategies, which are relevant to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also deals with the polysemy of named entities, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model presented in the paper that unifies linguistic and world knowledge is also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language understanding (cs.NE).
